---
globs: apps/web/**/*.ts, apps/web/**/*.tsx
alwaysApply: false
---

Use these rules for the apps/web Next.js application.

Framework:
- Use Next.js 15 App Router patterns.
- Use TypeScript for all new web files.
- Prefer Server Components by default.
- Use "use client" only when browser APIs, event handlers, local state, or real-time UI behavior are required.
- Use Server Actions or API routes where appropriate.
- Keep long-running work out of web requests.

UI:
- Use Tailwind CSS and shadcn/ui.
- Keep UI components in apps/web/components.
- Keep shared utilities in apps/web/lib.
- Handle loading, error, empty, and success states.
- Make job progress visible to users.
- For video/project detail pages, prioritize clarity: source video status, transcript status, highlights, generated clips, and job history.

API routes:
- POST /api/projects should create a project row and enqueue an ingest job.
- Job creation should happen in the database, not in memory.
- API routes should return quickly.
- API routes must never download, transcribe, analyze, or render long videos directly.
- Validate all incoming request bodies.
- Validate ownership/access before returning project, job, clip, or account data.
- Return structured JSON errors.

SSE:
- Use Server-Sent Events for live job status.
- SSE should stream job/project status changes from the database.
- Keep SSE responses lightweight.
- Include fallback behavior if SSE disconnects.

Do not:
- Store raw video data in React state.
- Store large media files in the database.
- Expose API keys or OAuth secrets to client components.
- Put Python worker logic in the Next.js app.
